HON_0016|I-123|generation|Which production method is correct?|Cyclotron|Mo-99/Tc-99m generator|I-123 is cyclotron-produced.|2
HON_0017|I-131|emission|Which emission profile is correct?|Beta-minus plus gamma emission|Pure positron emission|I-131 emits beta particles and gamma photons. The beta emission is useful therapeutically and the gamma emission allows imaging.|2
HON_0018|I-131|half_life|Which half-life is correct?|~8 days|~6 hours|I-131 has a physical half-life of approximately 8 days.|2
HON_0019|I-131|decay_mode|Which decay mode is correct?|Beta-minus decay|Electron capture|I-131 decays by beta-minus emission and also emits gamma photons.|2
HON_0020|I-131|common_use|Which use is correct?|Thyroid therapy and thyroid cancer treatment|Bone scan perfusion imaging|I-131 is used for treatment of hyperthyroidism and differentiated thyroid cancer.|2
